#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&klickety; is an adaptation of the Clickomania game. The rules are "
#| "similar to those of the Same game: your goal is to clear the board by "
#| "clicking on groups to destroy them. The overall aim is to get the lowest "
#| "score possible. It will provide entertainment for all abilities, but a "
#| "challenge in logical thought if you want to get a really low score."
msgid ""
"&klickety; is an adaptation of the <application>Clickomania</application> "
"game. The rules are similar to those of the <literal>Same</literal> game: "
"your goal is to clear the board by clicking on groups to destroy them. The "
"overall aim is to get the lowest score possible. It will provide "
"entertainment for all abilities, but a challenge in logical thought if you "
"want to get a really low score."
msgstr ""
"&klickety; é unha adaptación do xogo Clickomania. As regras son similares ás "
"do xogo Same: o obxectivo é limpar o taboleiro do xogo de todos os bloques "
"coloridos, premendo os grupos para os destruír. O obxectivo global é obter a "
"menor puntuación posíbel. Fornecerá entretemento para todas as aptitudes, "
"pero é un desafío de raciocinio lóxico se se quixer obter unha puntuación "
"realmente baixa."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Como xogar"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Obxectivo:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clear the game board of all the colored blocks in the least possible time."
msgstr ""
"Limpar o taboleiro de todas as pecas coloridas, no tempo mínimo posíbel."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start the program you will get a screen that looks something like "
"the screenshot in the previous section. The idea of the game is to remove "
"blocks, which you do by clicking on them."
msgstr ""
"Cando se inicia o programa, vese unha pantalla similar á imaxe da sección "
"anterior. A idea do xogo é retirar bloques, o que se fai preméndoos."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, you can only remove a block if it is adjacent to one or more other "
"blocks of the same color on one or more of its sides. Diagonal connections "
"do not count. You get a random board every time you start a new game."
msgstr ""
"Porén, só se pode retirar un bloque se estiver adxacente a un ou máis "
"bloques da mesma cor por unha ou máis caras. As ligazóns diagonais non "
"contan. De cada vez que se inicia un xogo obtense un taboleiro ao chou."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you click on a block which is connected as described, it will disappear. "
"Any adjacent blocks of the same color will also disappear, along with all of "
"the same color adjacent to <emphasis>them</emphasis>, and so on. Any blocks "
"above them drop down to fill the gaps left by the disappeared pieces. If you "
"clear an entire column, all the columns to the right move across to fill the "
"gap."
msgstr ""
"Se se preme un bloque que estea ligado da forma descrita, este desaparece. "
"Todos os bloques adxacentes da mesma cor, así como todos os da mesma cor "
"adxacentes a <emphasis>estes</emphasis> e así por diante. Todos os bloques "
"de enriba caen para encher os buracos deixados polas pezas que desaparecen. "
"Se se limpa unha columna enteira, todas as columnas á dereita móvense tamén "
"para encher o oco."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The game ends when there are no blocks adjacent to other blocks of the same "
"colour."
msgstr ""
"O xogo termina cando non houber máis bloques adxacentes a outros bloques da "
"mesma cor."

